main event: A civilian witness reported seeing a bright light in the sky to the west that appeared to be changing colors and moving erratically over Greenebay, Wisconsin on September 19, 1961.
interesting points: The witness reported the observation to the Greenebay Air Force Base.
The sighting was also detected on radar, with the object described as a 'round, large, silver' object at an altitude of 80-90,000 feet and stationary for 15 minutes.
The radar data showed the object changing direction, with estimates of its speed and course provided.
The investigation suggested the object's high velocity and erratic course ruled out it being a normal aircraft or weather balloon.
sighted object: a bright light in the sky that changed colors and moved erratically
